!.What is an IP Address?
 An IP address is a unique digital ID that lets devices find and talk to each other over a network.
2.Whta is difference between IPv4 and IPv6?
 IPv4 and IPv6 uses 32-bit addresses(4.3 billion)in dot-decimal notation,while IPv6 uses 128-bit addresses (340 undecillion) in hexadecimal ,offering masive capacity and built-in- security.
3.what is public vs private IP address?
 Public IP addresses are globally unique identifiers used to communicate over the internet ,assigned by ISPs.Private Ip addresses are used within local networks (homes/offices),asssigned by routers to identify devices(PCs,phones).
4.What is Localhost(127.0.0.1)?
 127.0.0.1 is the default loopback IPv4 address known as localhost,which allows your computer to connect itself,by passing physical network interfaces.
